e with Tien Nguyen and Natasha Phan. This dish uses the Sweet Garlic Teriyaki sauce you can find below." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Green bean and chicken stir-fry is one of the many "vegetable-forward" recipes in Roy Choi's cookbook, &lt;em&gt;The Choi of Cooking: Flavor-Packed, Rule-Breaking Recipes for a Delicious Life: A Cookbook, &lt;/em&gt;which he co-wrote with Tien Nguyen and Natasha Phan. This dish uses the Sweet Garlic Teriyaki sauce you can find below.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Bobby Fisher                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Check out what &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/sections/culture/" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NPR&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;strong&gt; is watching, reading and listening to this weekend:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;🍿 Movies:&lt;/strong&gt; No tricks, just treats when it comes to horror films released this year. In honor of the holiday, &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/10/30/nx-s1-5587657/horror-movies-halloween-scary-movies-weapons-sinners-good-boy" target="_blank"&gt;check out these films&lt;/a&gt; that range from supernatural to slightly-too-realistic, many of which you can watch from the comfort of your own home.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;📺 TV:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/09/17/nx-s1-5534152/what-to-watch-new-tv" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Talamasca: The Secret Order&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt; centers on the secret society that researches and monitors the supernatural elements of Anne Rice's fictional world.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;📚 Books:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/10/29/nx-s1-5587829/wreck-sandwich-sequel-catherine-newman" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Wreck&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt; &lt;/em&gt;follows up Catherine Newman's hit novel,&lt;em&gt; &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2024/06/17/nx-s1-5008714/when-women-ran-fifth-avenue-julie-satow-sandwich-catherine-newman-review" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Sandwich&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, by revisiting her beloved Rocky and her family. Life seems to be going as normally as possible until Rocky finds herself focused on a local train crash. Here are some other &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/10/28/nx-s1-5563791/new-books-zadie-smith-cameron-crowe-wreck-sandwich" target="_blank"&gt;new releases from this week&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;🎵 Music:&lt;/strong&gt; Are you really prepared for Halloween festivities without a great playlist? &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/10/21/nx-s1-5580266/redefining-the-halloween-canon" target="_blank"&gt;These songs are essential&lt;/a&gt; for the spooky season, ranging from truly terrifying to autumnal and nostalgic.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;🥦 Food:&lt;/strong&gt; Make your veggies more exciting to eat by trying the &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/10/25/nx-s1-5582638/3-culinary-tricks-get-you-to-eat-more-veggies-vegetables-chef-roy-choi" target="_blank"&gt;recipes for these three flavorful sauces&lt;/a&gt; from &lt;em&gt;The Choi of Cooking: Flavor-Packed, Rule-Breaking Recipes for a Delicious Life&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;❓ Quiz:&lt;/strong&gt; A "not too shabby" score of 7/11 again for me. Do you think you can do better than that? &lt;a href="http://npr.org/2025/10/31/g-s1-95763/trump-wikipedia-musk-shein-amazon-frankenstein-news-quiz" target="_blank"&gt;Give it a try&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;3 things to know before you go&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-95564" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 2231;         --source-height: 1255;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2231x1255+0+658/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Ffe%2Fe3%2Fafa4513247648f28cb79d576940f%2Fkids-with-boxes-1950.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2231x1255+0+658/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Ffe%2Fe3%2Fafa4513247648f28cb79d576940f%2Fkids-with-boxes-1950.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2231x1255+0+658/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Ffe%2Fe3%2Fafa4513247648f28cb79d576940f%2Fkids-with-boxes-1950.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2231x1255+0+658/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Ffe%2Fe3%2Fafa4513247648f28cb79d576940f%2Fkids-with-boxes-1950.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2231x1255+0+658/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Ffe%2Fe3%2Fafa4513247648f28cb79d576940f%2Fkids-with-boxes-1950.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2231x1255+0+658/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Ffe%2Fe3%2Fafa4513247648f28cb79d576940f%2Fkids-with-boxes-1950.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2231x1255+0+658/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Ffe%2Fe3%2Fafa4513247648f28cb79d576940f