3%2Fafa4513247648f28cb79d576940f%2Fkids-with-boxes-1950.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2231x1255+0+658/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Ffe%2Fe3%2Fafa4513247648f28cb79d576940f%2Fkids-with-boxes-1950.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2231x1255+0+658/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Ffe%2Fe3%2Fafa4513247648f28cb79d576940f%2Fkids-with-boxes-1950.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2231x1255+0+658/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Ffe%2Fe3%2Fafa4513247648f28cb79d576940f%2Fkids-with-boxes-1950.jpg" class="img" alt="tk" loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 tk                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          UNICEF USA                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;ol class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;This year marks the &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/sections/goats-and-soda/2025/10/30/g-s1-95543/halloween-trick-or-treat-candy-unicef-heidi-klum" target="_blank"&gt;75th anniversary of Trick-or-Treat for UNICEF&lt;/a&gt;, an initiative where children collect coins to donate to the agency that supports children in need worldwide. Since the initiative began, approximately $200 million has been collected.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;An ancient comet named 3I/ATLAS entered our solar system this summer, becoming only the &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/10/30/nx-s1-5591378/3i-atlas-comet-nickel-space" target="_blank"&gt;third interstellar object to do so&lt;/a&gt; in recorded history. The opportunity for scientists to observe this rare occurrence is valuable.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;A new look at the "Dueling Dinosaurs" fossil, which scientists previously believed was a Tyrannosaurus rex, reveals that it is actually a &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/10/30/nx-s1-5589172/tyrannosaurus-rex-dueling-dinosaurs-fossil-new-species" target="_blank"&gt;different tyrannosaur species&lt;/a&gt;: &lt;em&gt;Nanotyrannus lancensis&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;       &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;This newsletter was edited by &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/people/g-s1-2467/obed-manuel"target="_blank"   &gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Obed Manuel&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
