    <item>
      <title>Trump lowers China's tariffs. And, what to know for Casey Means' confirmation hearing</title>
      <author>Brittney Melton</author>
      <link>https://www.npr.org/2025/10/30/g-s1-95738/up-first-newsletter-trump-xi-jinping-head-start-deadline-casey-means</link>
      <comments>https://text.npr.org/2025/10/30/g-s1-95738/up-first-newsletter-trump-xi-jinping-head-start-deadline-casey-means</comments>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.npr.org/2025/10/30/g-s1-95738/up-first-newsletter-trump-xi-jinping-head-start-deadline-casey-means</guid>
      <pubDate>Thu, 30 Oct 2025 11:38:19 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;div id="storytext" class="storytext storylocation linkLocation"&gt;       &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Good morning. You're reading the Up First newsletter. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/newsletter/news" target="_blank"&gt;Subscribe&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt; here to get it delivered to your inbox, and &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/podcasts/510318/up-first/" target="_blank"&gt;listen&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt; to the Up First podcast for all the news you need to start your day.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;Today's top stories&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Today, President Trump and Chinese leader Xi Jinping met and reached an agreement on several points in trade negotiations.&lt;/strong&gt; Trump announced the U.S. would lower the 20% tariffs to 10% because China has committed to doing more to curb exports of ingredients for fentanyl. China will defer export controls on rare earths and resume buying U.S. soybeans. U.S. and Chinese economic officials &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/10/29/nx-s1-5589729/trump-xi-deal-south-korea-apec" target="_blank"&gt;ironed out the trade details&lt;/a&gt; in Malaysia last weekend.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-95731-1" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 3511;         --source-height: 1975;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3511x1975+0+183/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd9%2F76%2Ff50d4c3c4b928282dfcd0ff2bc16%2Fgettyimages-2244103333.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3511x1975+0+183/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd9%2F76%2Ff50d4c3c4b928282dfcd0ff2bc16%2Fgettyimages-2244103333.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3511x1975+0+183/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd9%2F76%2Ff50d4c3c4b928282dfcd0ff2bc16%2Fgettyimages-2244103333.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3511x1975+0+183/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd9%2F76%2Ff50d4c3c4b928282dfcd0ff2bc16%2Fgettyimages-2244103333.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3511x1975+0+183/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd9%2F76%2Ff50d4c3c4b928282dfcd0ff2bc16%2Fgettyimages-2244103333.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3511x1975+0+183/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd9%2F76%2Ff50d4c3c4b928282dfcd0ff2bc16%2Fgettyimages-2244103333.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3511x1975+0+183/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd9%2F76%2Ff50d4c3c4b928282dfcd0ff2bc16%2Fgettyimages-2244103333.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3511x1975+0+183/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd9%2F76%2Ff50d4c3c4b928282dfcd0ff2bc16%2Fgettyimages-2244103333.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3511x1975+0+183/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd9%2F76%2Ff50d4c3c4b928282dfcd0ff2bc16%2Fgettyimages-2244103333.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3511x1975+0+183/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd9%2F76%2Ff50d4c3c4b928282dfcd0ff2bc16%2Fgettyimages-2244103333.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3511x1975+0+183/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd9%2F76%2Ff50d4c3c4b928282dfcd0ff2bc16%2Fgettyimages-2244103333.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3511x1975+0+183/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd9%2F76%2Ff50d4c3c4b928282dfcd0ff2bc16%2Fgettyimages-2244103333.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3511x1975+0+183/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd9%2F76%2Ff50d4c3c4b928282dfcd0ff2bc16%2Fgettyimages-2244103333.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3511x1975+0+183/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd9%2F76%2Ff50d4c3c4b928282dfcd0ff2bc16%2Fgettyimages-2244103333.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3511x1975+0+183/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd9%2F76%2Ff50d4c3c4b928282dfcd0ff2bc16%2Fgettyimages-2244103333.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3511x1975+0+183/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd9%2F76%2Ff50d4c3c4b928282dfcd0ff2bc16%2Fgettyimages-2244103333.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3511x1975+0+183/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd9%2F76%2Ff50d4c3c4b928282dfcd0ff2bc16%2Fgettyimages-2244103333.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3511x1975+0+183/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd9%2F76%2Ff50d4c3c4b928282dfcd0ff2bc16%2Fgettyimages-2244103333.jpg" class="img" alt="President Trump and Chinese President Xi Jinping shake hands as they depart following a bilateral meeting at Gimhae Air Base on Oct. 30 in Busan, South Korea. " loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 President Trump and Chinese President Xi Jinping shake hands as they depart after a bilateral meeting at Gimhae Air Base on Oct. 30 in Busan, South Korea. Trump is meeting Xi for the first time since taking office for his second term, following months of growing tension between the two countries.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Andrew Harnik/Getty Images                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;ul class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;🎧 &lt;strong&gt;Xi and Trump met on the sideline of the Asia Pacific Economic Cooperation summit in South Korea. &lt;/strong&gt;Trump said he didn't come to South Korea for APEC or Korean issues, but to meet with the Chinese leader. On social media, Trump posted that the U.S. would resume testing nuclear weapons "on an equal basis" with Russia and China. NPR's Anthony Kuhn clarifies to &lt;em&gt;Up First&lt;/em&gt; that while Russia and China are upgrading and expanding their nuclear arsenals, neither country has tested atomic bombs since the 1990s. Kuhn adds that Xi has not responded to Trump's statement, but "couldn't have liked it much." Kuhn says if Trump's announcement was to try to pressure China into a conversation about arms control, it &lt;a href="https://one.npr.org/?sharedMediaId=nx-s1-5590732:nx-s1-mx-5783600" target="_blank"&gt;could have the opposite effect&lt;/a&gt; and result in an arms race.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;       &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;More than 65,000 infants, toddlers and preschoolers could lose access to their local Head Start centers&lt;/strong&gt; across the U.S. beginning Nov. 1 because of the government shutdown. The federal program provides &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/04/18/nx-s1-5368248/president-trump-head-start" target="_blank"&gt;childcare and early learning for&lt;/a&gt; low-income families. &lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;ul class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;🎧 &lt;strong&gt;Without federal dollars, 134 Head Start programs are rushing to find alternative funding&lt;/strong&gt;, NPR's Cory Turner says. If the programs close, many working families may have to &lt;a href="https://one.npr.org/?sharedMediaId=nx-s1-5590732:nx-s1-mx-5783600" target="_blank"&gt;choose between going to work and taking care of&lt;/a&gt; their children. Corey Holcomb, who runs a Head Start program in Michigan, told Turner that her agency secured two more weeks of funding by pulling from other resources with the hopes that they will be reimbursed. They've also asked for deferments on some bills.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Trump's pick for Surgeon General, Casey Means, will have her confirmation hearing in front of a Senate committee today. &lt;/strong&gt;The president announced that Means would replace his initial choice, a Fox News contributor, more than five months ago. Means is a wellness influencer and entrepreneur. Last year, she published the bestselling book &lt;em&gt;Good Energy&lt;/em&gt;. Here's &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/10/30/nx-s1-5589127/casey-means-confirmation-hearing-surgeon-general" target="_blank"&gt;what to watch for during the hearing&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;ul class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;🎧&lt;strong&gt; NPR's Will Stone says the hearing is somewhat unusual because it will be held virtually, and Means will join remotely. &lt;/strong&gt;Stone says he expects that she will be grilled about her qualifications and potential conflicts of interest. Some medical and public health professionals have pushed back on Means' confirmation. They have &lt;a href="https://one.npr.org/?sharedMediaId=nx-s1-5590732:nx-s1-mx-5783600" target="_blank"&gt;highlighted her lack of qualifications&lt;/a&gt;, and note that she dropped out of her surgical residency and does not have an active medical license. Critics argue that Means doesn't possess the leadership or clinical experience typically expected from the surgeon general, who is regarded as the nation's top doctor.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;       &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;Deep dive&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-95577" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 5280;         --source-height: 2970;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5280x2970+0+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F88%2F76%2Faf13cb344ca49659939bd1dfaeb1%2Fdiptych-3.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5280x2970+0+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F88%2F76%2Faf13cb344ca49659939bd1dfaeb1%2Fdiptych-3.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5280x2970+0+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F88%2F76%2Faf13cb344ca49659939bd1dfaeb1%2Fdiptych-3.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5280x2970+0+0/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F88%2F76%2Faf13cb344ca49659939bd1dfaeb1%2Fdiptych-3.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5280x2970+0+0/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F88%2F76%2Faf13cb344ca49659939bd1dfaeb1%2Fdiptych-3.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5280x2970+0+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F88%2F76%2Faf13cb344ca49659939bd1dfaeb1%2Fdiptych-3.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5280x2970+0+0/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F88%2F76%2Faf13cb344ca49659939bd1dfaeb1%2Fdiptych-3.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5280x2970+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F88%2F76%2Faf13cb344ca49659939bd1dfaeb1%2Fdiptych-3.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5280x2970+0+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F88%2F76%2Faf13cb344ca49659939bd1dfaeb1%2Fdiptych-3.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5280x2970+0+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F88%2F76%2Faf13cb344ca49659939bd1dfaeb1%2Fdiptych-3.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5280x2970+0+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F88%2F76%2Faf13cb344ca49659939bd1dfaeb1%2Fdiptych-3.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5280x2970+0+0/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F88%2F76%2Faf13cb344ca49659939bd1dfaeb1%2Fdiptych-3.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5280x2970+0+0/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F88%2F76%2Faf13cb344ca49659939bd1dfaeb1%2Fdiptych-3.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5280x2970+0+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F88%2F76%2Faf13cb344ca49659939bd1dfaeb1%2Fdiptych-3.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5280x2970+0+0/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F88%2F76%2Faf13cb344ca49659939bd1dfaeb1%2Fdiptych-3.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5280x2970+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F88%2F76%2Faf13cb344ca49659939bd1dfaeb1%2Fdiptych-3.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5280x2970+0+0/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F88%2F76%2Faf13cb344ca49659939bd1dfaeb1%2Fdiptych-3.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5280x2970+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F88%2F76%2Faf13cb344ca49659939bd1dfaeb1%2Fdiptych-3.jpg" class="img" alt="Over the past year, many federal law enforcement agents conducting immigration arrests have been concealing their faces under masks and vehicles being used in what appear to be immigration-related arrests do not have license plates." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Over the past year, many&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;federal law enforcement agents conducting immigration arrests have been concealing their faces under masks and vehicles being used in what appear to be immigration-related arrests do not have license plates.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Getty Images, Tik tok, Eyes Up                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;In the past year, many federal law enforcement agents conducting immigration arrests have hidden their identities. They have not only concealed their faces but have also masked their vehicles. NPR discovered through a review of videos that the vehicles used by officers during immigration-related arrests sometimes lacked license plates or had plates that were swapped out from their originals. Immigration advocates say that as U.S. Immigration and Customs Enforcement increases its presence across the U.S., untraceable vehicles may add to confusion over what tactics its officers can or should be using, and could &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/10/29/g-s1-95373/immigration-arrests-license-plates-conceal-federal-agents" target="_blank"&gt;prevent people from holding officers accountable&lt;/a&gt; for their actions. &lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;ul class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;🚨 ICE spokesperson Mike Alvarez informed NPR that &lt;a href="https://www.ecfr.gov/current/title-41/subtitle-C/chapter-102/subchapter-B/part-102-34/subpart-C/subject-group-ECFRcf796a305c40f05/section-102-34.175" target="_blank"&gt;federal regulations&lt;/a&gt; require government vehicles to display license plates on both the front and rear. However, this requirement can be waived if showing the plates would interfere with investigative, law enforcement, intelligence, or security operations.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;🚨 Some states prohibit swapping license plates on vehicles. However, photos taken by activists and videos shared on social media suggest that some federal agents are doing it anyway. Some activists have also spotted vehicles with a license plate on the front of a vehicle that doesn't match the one on the back.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;🚨 In Washington and Illinois, some videos shared on social media show federal agents making arrests in vehicles marked with Mexican objects or icons. When asked about this tactic, Department of Homeland Security spokesperson Tricia McLaughlin said that the agency believes its employees are not camouflaging their identities.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Read more about the &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/10/29/g-s1-95373/immigration-arrests-license-plates-conceal-federal-agents" target="_blank"&gt;tactics agents are using&lt;/a&gt; to make immigration arrests.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;Life advice&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-94684" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 3000;         --source-height: 1688;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+363/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F91%2F2c%2Fb943affd4f88a73a577130a233ff%2Flk-kc-davis-who-deserves-love-gettyimages-1270319496-copy.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+363/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F91%2F2c%2Fb943affd4f88a73a577130a233ff%2Flk-kc-davis-who-deserves-love-gettyimages-1270319496-copy.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+363/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F91%2F2c%2Fb943affd4f88a73a577130a233ff%2Flk-kc-davis-who-deserves-love-gettyimages-1270319496-copy.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+363/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F91%2F2c%2Fb943affd4f88a73a577130a233ff%2Flk-kc-davis-who-deserves-love-gettyimages-1270319496-copy.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+363/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F91%2F2c%2Fb943affd4f88a73a577130a233ff%2Flk-kc-davis-who-deserves-love-gettyimages-1270319496-copy.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+363/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F91%2F2c%2Fb943affd4f88a73a577130a233ff%2Flk-kc-davis-who-deserves-love-gettyimages-1270319496-copy.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+363/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F91%2F2c%2Fb943affd4f88a73a577130a233ff%2Flk-kc-davis-who-deserves-love-gettyimages-1270319496-copy.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+363/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F91%2F2c%2Fb943affd4f88a73a577130a233ff%2Flk-kc-davis-who-deserves-love-gettyimages-1270319496-copy.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+363/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F91%2F2c%2Fb943affd4f88a73a577130a233ff%2Flk-kc-davis-who-deserves-love-gettyimages-1270319496-copy.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+363/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazo