       &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Getty Images and via Bob Hinz/Emily Bogle/NPR                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;NPR's series &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/series/g-s1-89066/cost-of-living" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Cost of Living: The Price We Pay&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt; is examining what's driving price increases and how people are coping after years of stubborn inflation. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Sporting events are becoming a luxury due to increasing expenses. Many loyal fans have been priced out of attending these events, and the cost has more than doubled since the Labor Department started tracking sports ticket costs in 1999. Here's &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/10/23/nx-s1-5561909/ticket-prices-sports" target="_blank"&gt;why tickets cost so much&lt;/a&gt; now: &lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;ul class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;🎟️ Teams are hiking the prices because they prefer to sell fewer seats at a higher price point than more seats at a lower price.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;🎟️ Dynamic pricing, which allows vendors to adjust ticket prices based on demand, has allowed teams to get more money per ticket.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;🎟️ Teams are focusing more on selling premium seats and experiences, which include special club areas and the opportunity to stand on the sidelines.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Listen to learn more about the rising cost of &lt;a href="https://one.npr.org/?sharedMediaId=nx-s1-5561909:x" target="_blank"&gt;sports tickets&lt;/a&gt;. This week, the series will cover transportation, from buying a new vehicle to the price of car insurance. Stay up-to-date on the latest stories &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/series/g-s1-89066/cost-of-living" target="_blank"&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;How are higher prices changing the way you live? Fill out &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/09/12/g-s1-88442/cost-of-living-prices" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;em&gt;this form&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt; to share your story with NPR.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;Picture show&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-94689" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 1040;         --source-height: 585;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1040x585+0+220/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fab%2F5e%2Fc5972bab4262a2d898948c0743ca%2Fdrone-awards-2025-final-14.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1040x585+0+220/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fab%2F5e%2Fc5972bab4262a2d898948c0743ca%2Fdrone-awards-2025-final-14.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1040x585+0+220/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fab%2F5e%2Fc5972bab4262a2d898948c0743ca%2Fdrone-awards-2025-final-14.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1040x585+0+220/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fab%2F5e%2Fc5972bab4262a2d898948c0743ca%2Fdrone-awards-2025-final-14.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1040x585+0+220/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fab%2F5e%2Fc5972bab4262a2d898948c0743ca%2Fdrone-awards-2025-final-14.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1040x585+0+220/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fab%2F5e%2Fc5972bab4262a2d898948c0743ca%2Fdrone-awards-2025-final-14.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1040x585+0+220/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fab%2F5e%2Fc5972bab4262a2d898948c0743ca%2Fdrone-awards-2025-final-14.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1040x585+0+220/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fab%2F5e%2Fc5972bab4262a2d898948c0743ca%2Fdrone-awards-2025-final-14.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1040x585+0+220/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fab%2F5e%2Fc5972bab4262a2d898948c0743ca%2Fdrone-awards-2025-final-14.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1040x585+0+220/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fab%2F5e%2Fc5972bab4262a2d898948c0743ca%2Fdrone-awards-2025-final-14.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1040x585+0+220/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fab%2F5e%2Fc5972bab4262a2d898948c0743ca%2Fdrone-awards-2025-final-14.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1040x585+0+220/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fab%2F5e%2Fc5972bab4262a2d898948c0743ca%2Fdrone-awards-2025-final-14.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1040x585+0+220/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fab%2F5e%2Fc5972bab4262a2d898948c0743ca%2Fdrone-awards-2025-final-14.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1040x585+0+220/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fab%2F5e%2Fc5972bab4262a2d898948c0743ca%2Fdrone-awards-2025-final-14.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1040x585+0+220/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fab%2F5e%2Fc5972bab4262a2d898948c0743ca%2Fdrone-awards-2025-final-14.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1040x585+0+220/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fab%2F5e%2Fc5972bab4262a2d898948c0743ca%2Fdrone-awards-2025-final-14.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1040x585+0+220/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fab%2F5e%2Fc5972bab4262a2d898948c0743ca%2Fdrone-awards-2025-final-14.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1040x585+0+220/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fab%2F5e%2Fc5972bab4262a2d898948c0743ca%2Fdrone-awards-2025-final-14.jpg" class="img" alt="During the magic of blue hour, a lone rider stands atop a rocky outcropping in the heart of Cappadocia. Taken on the very first evening during Dennis&amp;#039; winter trip, this photo showcases the beauty and mystery of Cappadocia in all its glory. Using his drone, Dennis managed to find a unique and breathtaking perspective that had never been captured before in this often-photographed landscape." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 During the magic of blue hour, a lone rider stands atop a rocky outcropping in the heart of Cappadocia. Taken on the very first evening during Dennis' winter trip, this photo showcases the beauty and mystery of Cappadocia in all its glory. Using his drone, Dennis managed to find a unique and breathtaking perspective that had never been captured before in this often-photographed landscape.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Dennis Schmelz                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The 2025 Siena Awards is a global competition that celebrates the art of aerial photography captured by drones. The entries this year range from a photograph of a horseman at sunset in Turkey, spotted between large rocks that appeared to form a natural stage, to a bird's-eye view of thousands gathering at the Ganges River in India to celebrate the body of water as a source of life. Drone photography has allowed many people to see a new perspective and reveal patterns that are not visible from the ground, says Dennis Schmelz, a filmmaker based in Germany who took top honors in this year's awards. Here's a look at a &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/sections/goats-and-soda/2025/10/25/g-s1-94482/drone-photo-contest-winners" target="_blank"&gt;selection of award-winning and highly commended drone photographs&lt;/a&gt; from the Global South countries that &lt;em&gt;Goats &amp; Soda&lt;/em&gt; covers, plus an irresistible image from Italy.&lt;/p&gt;       &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;3 things to know before you go&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-94963" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 912;         --source-height: 513;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/912x513+0+175/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fe2%2Fba%2F2811b2614f1e9e8f03b5d870c7a4%2Ffrom-l-to-r-eric-schwartz-kurt-schwartz-jean-schwartz-bill-schwartz.jpeg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/912x513+0+175/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fe2%2Fba%2F2811b2614f1e9e8f03b5d870c7a4%2Ffrom-l-to-r-eric-schwartz-kurt-schwartz-jean-schwartz-bill-schwartz.jpeg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/912x513+0+175/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fe2%2Fba%2F2811b2614f1e9e8f03b5d870c7a4%2Ffrom-l-to-r-eric-schwartz-kurt-schwartz-jean-schwartz-bill-schwartz.jpeg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/912x513+0+175/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fe2%2Fba%2F2811b2614f1e9e8f03b5d870c7a4%2Ffrom-l-to-r-eric-schwartz-kurt-schwartz-jean-schwartz-bill-schwartz.jpeg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/912x513+0+175/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fe2%2Fba%2F2811b2614f1e9e8f03b5d870c7a4%2Ffrom-l-to-r-eric-schwartz-kurt-schwartz-jean-schwartz-bill-schwartz.jpeg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/912x513+0+175/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fe2%2Fba%2F2811b2614f1e9e8f03b5d870c7a4%2Ffrom-l-to-r-eric-schwartz-kurt-schwartz-jean-schwartz-bill-schwartz.jpeg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/912x513+0+175/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fe2%2Fba%2F2811b2614f1e9e8f03b5d870c7a4%2Ffrom-l-to-r-eric-schwartz-kurt-schwartz-jean-schwartz-bill-schwartz.jpeg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/912x513+0+175/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fe2%2Fba%2F2811b2614f1e9e8f03b5d870c7a4%2Ffrom-l-to-r-eric-schwartz-kurt-schwartz-jean-schwartz-bill-schwartz.jpeg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/912x513+0+175/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fe2%2Fba%2F2811b2614f1e9e8f03b5d870c7a4%2Ffrom-l-to-r-eric-schwartz-kurt-schwartz-jean-schwartz-bill-schwartz.jpeg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/912x513+0+175/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fe2%2Fba%2F2811b2614f1e9e8f03b5d870c7a4%2Ffrom-l-to-r-eric-schwartz-kurt-schwartz-jean-schwartz-bill-schwartz.jpeg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/912x513+0+175/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fe2%2Fba%2F2811b2614f1e9e8f03b5d870c7a4%2Ffrom-l-to-r-eric-schwartz-kurt-schwartz-jean-schwartz-bill-schwartz.jpeg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/912x513+0+175/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fe2%2Fba%2F2811b2614f1e9e8f03b5d870c7a4%2Ffrom-l-to-r-eric-schwartz-kurt-schwartz-jean-schwartz-bill-schwartz.jpeg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/912x513+0+175/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fe2%2Fba%2F2811b2614f1e9e8f03b5d870c7a4%2Ffrom-l-to-r-eric-schwartz-kurt-schwartz-jean-schwartz-bill-schwartz.jpeg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/912x513+0+175/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fe2%2Fba%2F2811b2614f1e9e8f03b5d870c7a4%2Ffrom-l-to-r-eric-schwartz-kurt-schwartz-jean-schwartz-bill-schwartz.jpeg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/912x513+0+175/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fe2%2Fba%2F2811b2614f1e9e8f03b5d870c7a4%2Ffrom-l-to-r-eric-schwartz-kurt-schwartz-jean-schwartz-bill-schwartz.jpeg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/912x513+0+175/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fe2%2Fba%2F2811b2614f1e9e8f03b5d870c7a4%2Ffrom-l-to-r-eric-schwartz-kurt-schwartz-jean-schwartz-bill-schwartz.jpeg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/912x513+0+175/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fe2%2Fba%2F2811b2614f1e9e8f03b5d870c7a4%2Ffrom-l-to-r-eric-schwartz-kurt-schwartz-jean-schwartz-bill-schwartz.jpeg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/912x513+0+175/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fe2%2Fba%2F2811b2614f1e9e8f03b5d870c7a4%2Ffrom-l-to-r-eric-schwartz-kurt-schwartz-jean-schwartz-bill-schwartz.jpeg" class="img" alt="(From left to right) Eric Schwartz, Kurt Schwartz, Jean Schwartz and Bill Schwartz." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 (From left to right) Eric Schwartz, Kurt Schwartz, Jean Schwartz and Bill Schwartz.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Schwartz family photo                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;ol class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;Eric Schwartz's mother died when he was 15. On his first day back at school, he didn't want to discuss the loss. However, as Schwartz was leaving his last class of the day, his choir teacher, Renato Vellutino, stood up from behind the piano and pulled him into a bear hug. Neither of them said anything, but the hug from his unsung hero changed his life, and Schwartz has since tried to &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/10/27/nx-s1-5585162/grief-teenager-kindness" target="_blank"&gt;pass along that kind gesture to others&lt;/a&gt; who may be in pain.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Authorities have &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/10/26/nx-s1-5586598/suspects-arrest-paris-louvre-museum-theft" target="_blank"&gt;arrested several suspects in the theft&lt;/a&gt; of crown jewels from the Louvre in Paris. According to the Paris prosecutor, authorities apprehended one suspect at Charles de Gaulle Airport on Saturday night.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Officials euthanized four gray wolves in Northern California after they said there were &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/10/26/nx-s1-5586746/california-gray-wolf-livestock-attacks-euthanized-cattle" target="_blank"&gt;unprecedented levels of attacks on livestock&lt;/a&gt;. The state has been working to mitigate the impact the wolf population's comeback has had on ranchers.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;This newsletter was edited by &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/people/859721331/suzanne-nuyen"target="_blank"   &gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Suzanne Nuyen&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
