5%2Fba%2Fc55866bd4ca2ba24992713a8f1ec%2Fargentina-edit-toshow29.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2160x1215+0+113/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fe5%2Fba%2Fc55866bd4ca2ba24992713a8f1ec%2Fargentina-edit-toshow29.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2160x1215+0+113/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fe5%2Fba%2Fc55866bd4ca2ba24992713a8f1ec%2Fargentina-edit-toshow29.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2160x1215+0+113/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fe5%2Fba%2Fc55866bd4ca2ba24992713a8f1ec%2Fargentina-edit-toshow29.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2160x1215+0+113/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fe5%2Fba%2Fc55866bd4ca2ba24992713a8f1ec%2Fargentina-edit-toshow29.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2160x1215+0+113/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fe5%2Fba%2Fc55866bd4ca2ba24992713a8f1ec%2Fargentina-edit-toshow29.jpg" class="img" alt="Cachitas Now!, una banda disidente, le canta a un público universitario y queer en La Plata. La vocalista es Melissa Lobos Cachitas Now!, a dissident band, sings to a university and queer audience in La Plata. Their singer is Melissa Lobos." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Cachitas Now!, una banda disidente, le canta a un público universitario y queer en La Plata. La vocalista es Melissa Lobos  Cachitas Now!, a dissident band, sings to a university and queer audience in La Plata. Their singer is Melissa Lobos.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          &lt;i&gt;Karla Gachet&lt;/i&gt;                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/series/g-s1-89583/cumbia-across-latin-america" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Cumbia Across Latin America&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt; is a visual report covering the people, places and cultures that keep this music genre alive in six countries.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;The history of Argentine cumbia cannot be analyzed without considering the role migration plays in the genre, says Luciano Rombolá, host of the radio program Cumbia de la Pura. Around the 1950s, the University of Buenos Aires welcomed foreign migrants, who could study for free, attracting many music students. Among the students was Mario Castellón from Costa Rica, who formed a group with two Colombians, a Peruvian and a Chilean to perform at a wedding. This collaboration led to the formation of Los Wawancó, one of Argentina's most iconic cumbia bands. Since then, other influences like chicha and huayno tropical from Bolivia, cachaca from Paraguay, cumbia chicheras, chacaloneras and norteñas from Peru and Colombian cumbia have made their way to Argentine cumbia. Learn more about Argentina's &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/sections/the-picture-show/2025/10/15/nx-s1-5549182/cumbia-in-argentina" target="_blank"&gt;influence on the genre of music&lt;/a&gt; and see &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/sections/the-picture-show/2025/10/15/nx-s1-5549182/cumbia-in-argentina" target="_blank"&gt;pictures of the vibrant culture developed&lt;/a&gt;. You can also &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/sections/the-picture-show/2025/10/15/g-s1-93275/argentina-la-reina-de-la-bailanta" target="_blank"&gt;read the article in Spanish&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;3 things to know before you go&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-94449" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 2947;         --source-height: 1658;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2947x1658+0+117/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa3%2F07%2Fc45439774e628d7f66b286d5ec1d%2Fmuseum-outside.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2947x1658+0+117/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa3%2F07%2Fc45439774e628d7f66b286d5ec1d%2Fmuseum-outside.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2947x1658+0+117/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa3%2F07%2Fc45439774e628d7f66b286d5ec1d%2Fmuseum-outside.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2947x1658+0+117/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa3%2F07%2Fc45439774e628d7f66b286d5ec1d%2Fmuseum-outside.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2947x1658+0+117/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa3%2F07%2Fc45439774e628d7f66b286d5ec1d%2Fmuseum-outside.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2947x1658+0+117/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa3%2F07%2Fc45439774e628d7f66b286d5ec1d%2Fmuseum-outside.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2947x1658+0+117/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa3%2F07%2Fc45439774e628d7f66b286d5ec1d%2Fmuseum-outside.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2947x1658+0+117/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa3%2F07%2Fc45439774e628d7f66b286d5ec1d%2Fmuseum-outside.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2947x1658+0+117/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa3%2F07%2Fc45439774e628d7f66b286d5ec1d%2Fmuseum-outside.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2947x1658+0+117/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa3%2F07%2Fc45439774e628d7f66b286d5ec1d%2Fmuseum-outside.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2947x1658+0+117/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa3%2F07%2Fc45439774e628d7f66b286d5ec1d%2Fmuseum-outside.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2947x1658+0+117/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa3%2F07%2Fc45439774e628d7f66b286d5ec1d%2Fmuseum-outside.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2947x1658+0+117/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa3%2F07%2Fc45439774e628d7f66b286d5ec1d%2Fmuseum-outside.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2947x1658+0+117/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa3%2F07%2Fc45439774e628d7f66b286d5ec1d%2Fmuseum-outside.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2947x1658+0+117/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa3%2F07%2Fc45439774e628d7f66b286d5ec1d%2Fmuseum-outside.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2947x1658+0+117/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa3%2F07%2Fc45439774e628d7f66b286d5ec1d%2Fmuseum-outside.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2947x1658+0+117/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa3%2F07%2Fc45439774e628d7f66b286d5ec1d%2Fmuseum-outside.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2947x1658+0+117/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa3%2F07%2Fc45439774e628d7f66b286d5ec1d%2Fmuseum-outside.jpg" class="img" alt="The outside of the Museum of Christian and Gospel Music from the street." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 The Museum of Christian and Gospel Music opened this month in Nashville.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Jewly Hight/Nashville Public Radio                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;ol class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;The Museum of Christian &amp; Gospel Music opened this month in Nashville. It is the first museum in the U.S. &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/10/19/nx-s1-5570842/a-new-museum-in-nashville-celebrates-gospel-musics-contribution-to-american-culture" target="_blank"&gt;designed to celebrate the diverse history&lt;/a&gt; of Christian music.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Billboard&lt;/em&gt; has updated its system for removing songs from the Hot 100 singles chart once they are too old to qualify as contemporary hits. The new measure has knocked &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/10/22/g-s1-94489/billboard-hot-100-chart-changes-songs" target="_blank"&gt;10 tracks off&lt;/a&gt; this week's chart.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;This week, Iceland recorded mosquitoes within its borders for the &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/10/22/nx-s1-5582748/iceland-mosquitoes-first-time" target="_blank"&gt;first time in the nation's history&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;This newsletter was edited by &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/people/859721331/suzanne-nuyen"target="_blank"   &gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Suzanne Nuyen&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
