npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1920x1080+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fb2%2F71%2F708c42fe4408b2db39204fa6387e%2F20251020-me-jeanpierre-2-00-26-32-11-still001.png" class="img" alt="Karine Jean-Pierre gives an interview on her new book &amp;quot;Independent: A Look Inside a Broken White House, Outside the Party Lines&amp;quot;." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Karine Jean-Pierre gives an interview on her new book "Independent: A Look Inside a Broken White House, Outside the Party Lines".                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Bronson Arcuri/NPR                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Former White House press secretary Karine Jean-Pierre, who served during the Biden administration, has released her new book, &lt;em&gt;Independent: A Look Inside a Broken White House, Outside the Party Lines&lt;/em&gt;. She wrote about how the Democratic Party's internal dysfunction led to its downfall during the 2024 presidential election. Before her new book hit store shelves, &lt;em&gt;Morning Edition &lt;/em&gt;host Michel Martin sat down with Jean-Pierre. During their conversation, Jean-Pierre reflected on her decision to leave the party she once represented and the scrutiny she faced in her role as press secretary. Watch their interview &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/10/21/nx-s1-5423318/karine-jean-pierre-biden-book-democrats" target="_blank"&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;. Listen to Jean-Pierre discuss her &lt;a href="https://one.npr.org/?sharedMediaId=nx-s1-5423318:nx-s1-9499842" target="_blank"&gt;decision to identify as an independent&lt;/a&gt; and read &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/10/21/nx-s1-5423318/karine-jean-pierre-biden-book-democrats" target="_blank"&gt;five takeaways from the conversation&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;Life advice&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-91939" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 6016;         --source-height: 3384;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6016x3384+0+542/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F04%2Ff6%2F2b4142cf4758bbd71381972335b4%2Fgettyimages-1754488912.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6016x3384+0+542/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F04%2Ff6%2F2b4142cf4758bbd71381972335b4%2Fgettyimages-1754488912.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6016x3384+0+542/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F04%2Ff6%2F2b4142cf4758bbd71381972335b4%2Fgettyimages-1754488912.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6016x3384+0+542/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F04%2Ff6%2F2b4142cf4758bbd71381972335b4%2Fgettyimages-1754488912.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6016x3384+0+542/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F04%2Ff6%2F2b4142cf4758bbd71381972335b4%2Fgettyimages-1754488912.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6016x3384+0+542/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F04%2Ff6%2F2b4142cf4758bbd71381972335b4%2Fgettyimages-1754488912.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6016x3384+0+542/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F04%2Ff6%2F2b4142cf4758bbd71381972335b4%2Fgettyimages-1754488912.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6016x3384+0+542/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F04%2Ff6%2F2b4142cf4758bbd71381972335b4%2Fgettyimages-1754488912.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6016x3384+0+542/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F04%2Ff6%2F2b4142cf4758bbd71381972335b4%2Fgettyimages-1754488912.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6016x3384+0+542/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F04%2Ff6%2F2b4142cf4758bbd71381972335b4%2Fgettyimages-1754488912.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6016x3384+0+542/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F04%2Ff6%2F2b4142cf4758bbd71381972335b4%2Fgettyimages-1754488912.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6016x3384+0+542/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F04%2Ff6%2F2b4142cf4758bbd71381972335b4%2Fgettyimages-1754488912.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6016x3384+0+542/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F04%2Ff6%2F2b4142cf4758bbd71381972335b4%2Fgettyimages-1754488912.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6016x3384+0+542/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F04%2Ff6%2F2b4142cf4758bbd71381972335b4%2Fgettyimages-1754488912.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6016x3384+0+542/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F04%2Ff6%2F2b4142cf4758bbd71381972335b4%2Fgettyimages-1754488912.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6016x3384+0+542/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F04%2Ff6%2F2b4142cf4758bbd71381972335b4%2Fgettyimages-1754488912.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6016x3384+0+542/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F04%2Ff6%2F2b4142cf4758bbd71381972335b4%2Fgettyimages-1754488912.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6016x3384+0+542/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F04%2Ff6%2F2b4142cf4758bbd71381972335b4%2Fgettyimages-1754488912.jpg" class="img" alt="A photograph shows hot coffee being poured simultaneously into two burnt orange coffee mugs on a white countertop. Steam rises from the mugs. " loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Grab a mug! It's fall now.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Stefania Pelfini la Waziya/Getty Images                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;From vibrantly colored leaves to comforting weather, fall is a favorite season for many people. With all the excitement the season brings, you might feel anxious about making the most of this time of year.&lt;em&gt; Life Kit &lt;/em&gt;has put together a &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/10/04/g-s1-91330/8-low-effort-ways-to-make-spooky-season-feel-cozy-and-festive" target="_blank"&gt;list of simple ideas to help&lt;/a&gt; make the lead-up to Halloween feel festive. &lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;ul class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;🍂 Make simple adjustments as the days shorten, like switching from a cold breakfast to a warm one or lighting candles, to prepare your nest.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;🍂 When decorating, think about your commitment to putting away the decorations. This could be especially important as the end-of-the-year holidays approach.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;🍂 Don't feel pressured to find the perfect Halloween costume. It can be fun to try something unexpected, like dressing up as an inanimate object. Have you ever considered being a fruit or a bottle of Windex?&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;       &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;For tips on how to embrace a lifestyle of rest and coziness, &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://one.npr.org/?sharedMediaId=1128960386:1129441178" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;em&gt;listen to this episode of NPR's &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a href="https://one.npr.org/?sharedMediaId=1128960386:1129441178" target="_blank"&gt;Life Kit&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt;. Subscribe to &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/newsletter/life-kit" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;em&gt;the &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/newsletter/life-kit" target="_blank"&gt;Life Kit&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/newsletter/life-kit" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;em&gt; newsletter&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt; for expert advice on love, money, relationships and more.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;3 things to know before you go&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-94371" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 3000;         --source-height: 1688;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+105/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F03%2F98%2F5b08f7e447fdaa31854d817d6f51%2Fap25289687694338.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+105/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F03%2F98%2F5b08f7e447fdaa31854d817d6f51%2Fap25289687694338.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+105/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F03%2F98%2F5b08f7e447fdaa31854d817d6f51%2Fap25289687694338.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+105/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F03%2F98%2F5b08f7e447fdaa31854d817d6f51%2Fap25289687694338.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+105/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F03%2F98%2F5b08f7e447fdaa31854d817d6f51%2Fap25289687694338.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+105/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F03%2F98%2F5b08f7e447fdaa31854d817d6f51%2Fap25289687694338.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+105/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F03%2F98%2F5b08f7e447fdaa31854d817d6f51%2Fap25289687694338.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+105/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F03%2F98%2F5b08f7e447fdaa31854d817d6f51%2Fap25289687694338.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+105/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F03%2F98%2F5b08f7e447fdaa31854d817d6f51%2Fap25289687694338.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+105/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F03%2F98%2F5b08f7e447fdaa31854d817d6f51%2Fap25289687694338.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+105/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F03%2F98%2F5b08f7e447fdaa31854d817d6f51%2Fap25289687694338.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+105/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F03%2F98%2F5b08f7e447fdaa31854d817d6f51%2Fap25289687694338.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+105/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F03%2F98%2F5b08f7e447fdaa31854d817d6f51%2Fap25289687694338.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+105/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F03%2F98%2F5b08f7e447fdaa31854d817d6f51%2Fap25289687694338.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+105/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F03%2F98%2F5b08f7e447fdaa31854d817d6f51%2Fap25289687694338.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+105/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F03%2F98%2F5b08f7e447fdaa31854d817d6f51%2Fap25289687694338.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+105/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F03%2F98%2F5b08f7e447fdaa31854d817d6f51%2Fap25289687694338.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+105/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F03%2F98%2F5b08f7e447fdaa31854d817d6f51%2Fap25289687694338.jpg" class="img" alt="Researchers say fewer children developed peanut allergies after guidelines were put into place calling for introducing peanut products to young children." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Researchers say fewer children developed peanut allergies after guidelines were put into place calling for introducing peanut products to young children.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Patrick Sison/AP                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;ol class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;A new study in the journal &lt;em&gt;Pediatrics&lt;/em&gt; reveals that a &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/10/21/nx-s1-5580211/peanut-allergy-study" target="_blank"&gt;reversal in health guidance&lt;/a&gt; for when to feed babies peanuts helped prevent tens of thousands of peanut allergy cases in children under 3 in the U.S.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;The 2026 Sundance Film Festival &lt;a href="https://www.kpcw.org/park-city/2025-10-21/sundance-announces-park-city-legacy-program-for-2026-festival" target="_blank"&gt;will honor its founder&lt;/a&gt;, Robert Redford, who died in September at the age of 89. January's event will also include a Park City legacy program with film screenings from previous editions and artist talks. (via &lt;a href="https://www.kpcw.org/" target="_blank"&gt;KPCW&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;A federal judge has ordered the Department of Defense to &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/10/21/nx-s1-5580738/judge-banned-books-returned-to-military-school-libraries" target="_blank"&gt;return books about gender and race&lt;/a&gt; to five school libraries on military bases, following claims that the removal violated students' First Amendment rights.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;This newsletter was edited by &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/people/859721331/suzanne-nuyen"target="_blank"   &gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Suzanne Nuyen&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
